I also noticed that propName was being capitalized three times in the createComparatorFor() method, so I only call it once at the beginning.

I followed the same style of passing in the CharSequence like it was defined in the deprecated method:
```groovy
@Deprecated
public static String capitalize(String self) {
    return capitalize((CharSequence) self);
}
````

If you would rather have something like the following, or something else let me know:
```groovy
CharSequence propName = property.getName();
String capitalizedPropName = StringGroovyMethods.capitalize(propName);

```

[GROOVY-8261](https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/GROOVY-8261)

While debugging a `CompilationCustomizer` I noticed some cases where `getText` was less than helpful.

@reviewbybees for my colleagues

The idea is to create a simple http client without extra dependencies that will cover rest client needs.

Code example:
```groovy
def r = HTTP.get(
  url : 'https://www.googleapis.com/customsearch/v1',
  query: [ q: 'hello world' ],
  headers: [
    'Accept':'application/json',
    //'Authorization' : ...,
  ],
  //optional - ssl context 
  ssl : getNaiveSSLContext(),
  //optional - receiver
  receiver : { stream,context -> new JsonParser().parse(stream) },
  //optional - body
)
assert r.response.code == 200
println r.response.body

```
